The present study shows that SFE and solvent extraction
methods have both advantages and disadvantages for the
extraction of the essential oil and volatile oil components.
Based on the results, SFE has been proven to be an efficient
method of extraction. Solvent extraction can be utilized in
extraction of some compounds, such as TQ. The present study
also demonstrated that SFE is more efficient for extraction of
L. seed compared to the solvent
extraction technique. The essential oil obtained from SFE
process contained more LA than that achieved by solvent
extraction. It was observed that the oil extraction efficiency
obtained from SFE is higher than that achieved by solvent
extraction technique. According to this research,
